{
  "doc_id": "7474",
  "text": "One limitation of previous studies on genetic susceptibility to cocaine dependence, as well as to other complex disorders, is that known polymorphisms may explain only a small fraction of the heritability variance in cocaine dependence. Therefore, there is a need for studies investigating putative additional genetic markers associated with susceptibility to cocaine dependence, in particular those that might be specific to this disorder [CITATION_1] .",
